		<body>
			<div type="transcription">
				<div type="original" xml:lang="de">
					<pb facs="EHRI-DC-061_01.png" n="1"/>
					<p>Protokoll Nr. 9</p>
					<p><date when="1945-08-12">12. 8. 1945</date></p>
					<p>Protokoll</p>
					<p>aufgenommen mit <persName ref="#ehri_dc_winter_josef">Winter Josef</persName>, geboren am <date when="1897-10-25">25. 10. 1897</date>, Schäfer am <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-729" type="subject">Gut</term> des <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-729" type="subject">Stift-</term>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-728" type="subject">Kloster</term> Město <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/3070820/mesto.html">Teplá</placeName>, <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/2926950/fichtenhof.html">Fichterhof</placeName>,
							<placeName ref="https://www.geonames.org/3078198/cechy.html">Böhmen</placeName>, Nationalität deutsch.</p>
					<p><persName ref="#ehri_dc_winter_josef">Winter Josef</persName> gibt über den sogenannten <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-517" type="subject">Totenmarsch</term>, der <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/3070820/mesto.html">Teplá</placeName>
						passierte, folgendes an:</p>
					<p>Schon Anfang <date when="1945-04">April</date> konnte man auf der Straße Richtung <placeName ref="https://www.geonames.org/3064919/stribro.html">Mies</placeName> verschiedene <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-522" type="subject">Häftlingszüge</term>
						bemerken. Keiner dieser <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-522" type="subject">Züge</term> hielt aber in <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/3070820/mesto.html">Teplá</placeName>. Erst am <date when="1945-04-23">23.</date>, <date
							when="1945-04-24">24.</date> und <date when="1945-04-25">25. April</date> /: <persName ref="#ehri_dc_winter_josef">Winter</persName> kontrolliert die Daten laut seinem Tagebuch :/ hielten verschiedene <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-521"
							type="subject">Transporte</term> in der Nähe des <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-729" type="subject">Stift</term>
						<placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/3070820/mesto.html">Teplá</placeName>. Ein <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1216" type="subject">SS-Offizier</term>, dessen Namen <persName ref="#ehri_dc_winter_josef">Winter</persName> nicht kennt, führte
						mit dem Baumeister des <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-729" type="subject">Stifts</term> namens <persName ref="#ehri_dc_kroy_frantisek">Kroy</persName> die Einteilung der <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-650"
							type="subject">Häftlinge</term> in verschiedene <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-837" type="subject">Scheuen</term> der umliegenden <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-837" type="subject">Gutshöfe</term> zum <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-831" type="subject">Übernachten</term> durch. Dies geschah am <date when="1945-04-23">23.</date> abends. Zu <persName ref="#ehri_dc_winter_josef">Winter</persName> kam eine Gruppe jüdischer <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-825" type="subject">Frauen</term> verschiedener Nationalität. Die <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-825" type="subject">Frauen</term> waren in furchtbarem Zustand. Sie besaßen fast
						durchwegs mangelhaftes <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-836" type="subject">Schuhwerk</term>, waren in <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-836" type="subject">Lumpen</term> gehüllt, besaßen nicht einmal die primitivsten
						Gegenstände des täglichen Gebrauches und ihr einziges Gepäck war eine Decke, die oft auch das <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-836" type="subject">Kleid</term> ersetzte. Sie waren kahlgeschoren und es waren viele <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/terezin-terms-keyword-jmp-760" type="subject">Kranke</term> darunter, <persName ref="#ehri_dc_winter_josef">Winter</persName> wurde vor <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-493" type="subject"
							>Typhus</term> gewarnt. Die <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-650" type="subject">Häftlinge</term> wurde von weiblichen <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-478" type="subject">Aufseherinnen</term> vor den Augen des
							<persName ref="#ehri_dc_winter_josef">Winter</persName> und seiner <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-825" type="subject">Frau</term>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-562" type="subject">misshandelt</term> und mit Rufen <q>Rein, rein</q> in die <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-837" type="subject">Scheunen</term> gejagt. <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-825" type="subject">Frau</term>
						<persName ref="#ehri_dc_winter_hedwig">Winter</persName>, durch dieses Bild entsetzt, wollte einigen <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-825" type="subject">Frauen</term> helfen. Als dies eine <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-478" type="subject">Aufseherin</term> bemerkte, rief sie ihr zu: <q>Willst mit?</q> und jagte die <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-650" type="subject">Häftlinge</term> fort. <persName
							ref="#ehri_dc_winter_josef">Winter</persName> schätzt die Zahl der <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-650" type="subject">Häftlinge</term>, die bei ihm <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-831" type="subject"
							>übernachtet</term> haben, auf ca 320. Aus den kurzen Gesprächen, die er und <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-822" type="subject">Mitglieder</term> seiner <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-819" type="subject"
							>Familie</term> mit den <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-650" type="subject">Häftlingen</term> führten, ist ihm bekannt, dass die meisten eine langjährige <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-496" type="subject"
							>K-Z</term> Qual hinter sich hatten. Sie kamen aus <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-0" type="camp">Auschwitz</placeName>, <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-43" type="camp">Buchenwald</placeName>,
							<placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-760" type="camp">Ravensbrück</placeName> und anderen großen <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-496" type="subject">Konzentrationslagern</term>. Sie erzählten unter anderem, dass
						es ihnen in manchen <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-496" type="subject">Konzentrationslagern</term>, wo sie in <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-929" type="subject">Fabriken</term>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-556" type="subject"> arbeiteten</term>, etwas besser ging, dass aber, seitdem sie <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-623" type="subject">evakuiert</term> werden, keinerlei geregelte
						Verpflegung existiere, über die Hälfte der <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-650" type="subject">Häftlinge</term> bereits <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-745" type="subject">gestorben</term> ist oder unterwegs <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-532" type="subject">erschlagen</term> wurde und für viele der <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-745" type="subject">Tod</term> eine Erlösung war. Hingegen ist es <persName
							ref="#ehri_dc_winter_josef">Winter</persName> selbst nicht bekannt, dass im <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-837" type="subject">Raume</term> von <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/3070820/mesto.html">Teplá</placeName> irgendjemand vom
							<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-522" type="subject">Häftlingszuge</term>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-532" type="subject">erschlagen</term> wurde. Aus eigener Initiative, gibt <persName ref="#ehri_dc_winter_josef">Winter</persName> an, hätte er für die <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/terezin-terms-keyword-jmp-760" type="subject">Kranken</term> eine <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-832" type="subject">Suppe gekocht</term>, deren Verteilung eine <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-478" type="subject">Aufseherin</term> verhindern wollte, was jedoch nicht gelang. Laut Auftrag wurden für alle <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-650" type="subject">Häftlinge</term>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-832" type="subject">Kartoffeln</term> gekocht. <persName ref="#ehri_dc_winter_josef">Winter</persName> erinnert sich auch noch an folgende Szenen:</p>
					<p>Als ein Teil der <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-650" type="subject">Häftlinge</term> erschöpft auf den Boden sank und mit <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-562" type="subject">Schlägen</term> in die <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-837" type="subject">Scheune</term> gejagt wurde, hörte er einen <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1188" type="subject">Scharführer</term> sagen: <q>Jetzt habe ich aber genug.</q> Mit
						diesen Worten, so sagt <persName ref="#ehri_dc_winter_josef">Winter</persName>, hätte der <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1438" type="subject">Aufseher</term> seinen Entschluss kundgegeben, den <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-522" type="subject">Zug</term> zu verlassen und zu desertieren, da es auch für ihn schon zu stark war.</p>
					<p>Am <date when="1945-04-25">25. 4. 1945</date> kam ein weiterer <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-522" type="subject">Zug</term> von <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-650" type="subject">Häftlingen</term>, diesmal <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-826" type="subject">Männer</term>, in weitaus besserem Zustand: gestreifte <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-836" type="subject">Kleidung</term>, verschiedene Nationalitäten, aber keine
						Juden und verlangten <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-831" type="subject">Übernachtungsmöglichkeit</term>. <persName ref="#ehri_dc_winter_josef">Winter</persName> verweigerte dies mit der Begründung, die <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-837" type="subject">Scheunen</term> seien verseucht und er hätte noch keine Gelegenheit gehabt, sie zu reinigen. Um Ansteckung zu verhindern, schickte er sie auf ein anderes <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-729" type="subject">Stiftsgut</term>.</p>
					<pb facs="EHRI-DC-061_02.png" n="2"/>
					<p>Schließlich gibt <persName ref="#ehri_dc_winter_josef">Winter</persName> an, dass ihm viele der <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-650" type="subject">Häftlinge</term> versprochen hätten, zu schreiben, doch hätte er bis nun keinerlei Nachricht
						bekommen. Er hätte nie gedacht, dass so etwas im <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1159" type="subject">Deutschen Reiche</term> möglich wäre.</p>
					<p>Das Protokoll wurde durch <persName ref="#ehri_dc_shek_zeev">W. Zeew Scheck</persName> in Anwesenheit des Herrn <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-886" type="subject">Oberleutnant</term>
						<persName ref="#ehri_dc_singer_robert_m">Singer</persName>, des Fräulein <persName ref="#ehri_dc_ternerova_dorit">Dorit Terner</persName> und der <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-825" type="subject">Frau</term> des <persName
							ref="#ehri_dc_winter_josef">Josef Winter</persName> aufgenommen, was die Genannten durch eigenhändige Unterschrift hiemit bezeugen.</p>
					<p>Namen der Zeugen und Geburtsdaten:</p>
					<p><persName ref="#ehri_dc_shek_zeev">William Zeev Scheck</persName>
						<date when="1920-05-13">13. 5. 1920</date></p>
					<p><persName ref="#ehri_dc_winter_josef">Winter Josef</persName>
						<date when="1897-10-25">25. 10. 1897</date></p>
					<p><persName ref="#ehri_dc_winter_josef">Hedwig Winter</persName>
						<date when="1891-10-08">8. 10. 1891</date></p>
					<p><persName ref="#ehri_dc_singer_robert_m">Robert M. Singer</persName> Lt. Rus <date when="1919-11-22">22. 11. 1919</date></p>
					<p><persName ref="#ehri_dc_ternerova_dorit">Ternerová Dorit</persName>
						<date when="1925-09-28">28. 9. 1925</date></p>
				</div>
				<div type="translation" xml:lang="en">
					<pb facs="EHRI-DC-061_01.png" n="1"/>
					<p>Protocol No. 9</p>
					<p><date when="1945-08-12">12. 8. 1945</date></p>
					<p>Protocol</p>
					<p>recorded with <persName ref="#ehri_dc_winter_josef">Winter Josef</persName>, born <date when="1897-10-25">25. 10. 1897</date>, worker at the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-729" type="subject">estate of the Monastery</term>, town of <placeName
							ref="http://www.geonames.org/3070820/mesto.html">Teplá</placeName>, <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/2926950/fichtenhof.html">Fichterhof</placeName>, <placeName ref="https://www.geonames.org/3078198/cechy.html">Bohemia</placeName>, nationality German.</p>
					<p><persName ref="#ehri_dc_winter_josef">Winter Josef</persName> recounts the following about the so-called <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-517" type="subject">death march</term> that passed <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/3070820/mesto.html"
							>Teplá</placeName>:</p>
					<p>Already at the beginning of <date when="1945-04">April</date>, several <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-522" type="subject">prisoner trains</term> could be seen on the road to <placeName ref="https://www.geonames.org/3064919/stribro.html"
							>Mies</placeName>. None of these <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-522" type="subject">trains</term> stopped in <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/3070820/mesto.html">Teplá</placeName>. It was not until the <date when="1945-04-23"
							>23rd</date>, <date when="1945-04-24">24th</date> and <date when="1945-04-25">25th of April</date>/: <persName ref="#ehri_dc_winter_josef">Winter</persName> checks the dates in his diary: /that various <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-521"
							type="subject">transports</term> stopped near the <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/3070820/mesto.html">Teplá</placeName>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-728" type="subject">Abbey</term>. An <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1216" type="subject">SS officer</term>, whose name <persName ref="#ehri_dc_winter_josef">Winter</persName> does not
						know, with <persName ref="#ehri_dc_kroy_frantisek">Kroy</persName>, the Baumeister of the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-729" type="subject">abbey</term>, divided the inmates into the <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-837" type="subject">barns</term> of the surrounding <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-837" type="subject">manors</term> to stay <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-831" type="subject">overnight</term>. This happened on the evening of the <date when="1945-04-23">23rd</date>. A group of Jewish <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-825" type="subject"
							>women</term> of various nationalities came to <persName ref="#ehri_dc_winter_josef">Winter</persName>. The <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-825" type="subject">women</term> were in terrible condition. They had <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-836" type="subject">footwear</term> that was almost entirely inadequate, were wrapped in <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-836" type="subject">rags</term>, possessed not even the most
						primitive objects of daily use, and their only luggage was a blanket that often served as a <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-836" type="subject">dress</term>. Their heads were shaved and many were <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/terezin-terms-keyword-jmp-760" type="subject">ill</term>, and <persName ref="#ehri_dc_winter_josef">Winter</persName> was warned about <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-493" type="subject"
							>Typhus</term>. The <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-650" type="subject">inmates</term> were abused by <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-478" type="subject">female guards</term> in front of <persName
							ref="#ehri_dc_winter_josef">Winter</persName> and his <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-825" type="subject">wife</term> and chased into the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-837" type="subject">barns</term> with
						shouts of <q>get in, get in.</q> Mrs. <persName ref="#ehri_dc_winter_hedwig">Winter</persName>, appalled by this picture, wanted to help some of the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-825" type="subject">women</term>. When one of the <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-478" type="subject">guards</term> noticed, she called out, <q>wanna join in?</q> and kept chasing the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-650" type="subject">inmates</term> in. <persName
							ref="#ehri_dc_winter_josef">Winter</persName> estimates the number of <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-650" type="subject">inmates</term> who stayed the night with him at around 320. From the short conversations that he and <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-822" type="subject">members</term> of his <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-819" type="subject">family</term> had with the <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-650" type="subject">inmates</term>, he learned that most had long years of suffering in <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-496" type="subject">concentration camps</term> behind them. They
						came from <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-0" type="camp">Auschwitz</placeName>, <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-43" type="camp">Buchenwald</placeName>, <placeName
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-760" type="camp">Ravensbrück</placeName> and other large <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-496" type="subject">concentration camps</term>. Among other things, they said that in some <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-496" type="subject">concentration camps</term> where they <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-556" type="subject">worked</term> in factories, things were a little better, but that since they
						had been <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-623" type="subject">evacuated</term> there had been no proper food, more than half of the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-650" type="subject">inmates</term> had already <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-745" type="subject">died</term> or <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-532" type="subject">been killed</term> on the way, and that for many <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-745" type="subject">death</term> was a relief. On the other hand, <persName ref="#ehri_dc_winter_josef">Winter</persName> himself is not aware of anyone from the <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-650" type="subject">inmate</term> trains who was <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-532" type="subject">killed</term> in the <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/3070820/mesto.html"
							>Teplá</placeName>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-837" type="subject">area</term>. On his own initiative, says <persName ref="#ehri_dc_winter_josef">Winter</persName>, he <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-832" type="subject"
							>cooked</term>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-832" type="subject">soup</term> for those who were <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/terezin-terms-keyword-jmp-760" type="subject">ill</term>, and a <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-478" type="subject">female guard</term> tried to prevent it from being distributed, but did not succeed. According to the order, <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-832" type="subject"
							>potatoes</term> were cooked for all <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-650" type="subject">inmates</term>. <persName ref="#ehri_dc_winter_josef">Winter</persName> also remembers the following scenes:</p>
					<p>When some of the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-650" type="subject">inmates</term>, exhausted, sank to the ground and were chased into the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-837" type="subject">barn</term> with <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-562" type="subject">blows</term>, he heard a <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1188" type="subject">squad leader</term> say: <q>Now I have had enough.</q> With these words, <persName
							ref="#ehri_dc_winter_josef">Winter</persName> says, the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1438" type="subject">overseer</term> announced his intention to leave the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-522"
							type="subject">train</term> and to desert, because it was already too much for him.</p>
					<p>On <date when="1945-04-25">25. 4. 1945</date> came another <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-522" type="subject">train</term> of <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-650" type="subject">inmates</term>, this time men, in much
						better condition: striped <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-836" type="subject">clothes</term>, different nationalities, but no Jews and demanded overnight accommodation. <persName ref="#ehri_dc_winter_josef">Winter</persName> refused on the
						grounds that the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-837" type="subject">barns</term> were contaminated and he had not yet had a chance to clean them. To prevent infection, he sent her to another <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-729" type="subject">monastery estate</term>.</p>
					<pb facs="EHRI-DC-061_02.png" n="2"/>
					<p>Finally, <persName ref="#ehri_dc_winter_josef">Winter</persName> states that many of the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-650" type="subject">inmates</term> promised to write, but he has not received any news yet. He never thought that such a thing
						would be possible in the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1159" type="subject">German Reich</term>.</p>
					<p>The protocol was recorded by <persName ref="#ehri_dc_shek_zeev">W. Zeew Scheck</persName> in the presence of Herr <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-886" type="subject">Lieutenant</term>
						<persName ref="#ehri_dc_singer_robert_m">Singer</persName>, Miss <persName ref="#ehri_dc_ternerova_dorit">Dorit Terner</persName> and the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-825" type="subject">wife</term> of <persName ref="#ehri_dc_winter_josef"
							>Josef Winter</persName>, which the witnesses hereby attest by handwritten signature.</p>
